'''September 18''' is the 18th day of month {{ill|September (Lunisolar)|ja|9月 (旧暦)|lt=September (Nagatsuki)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}, the 9th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} day is {{ill|Tomobiki|ja|友引|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}.

== Events ==
* {{ill|Wadō|ja|和銅|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} 4th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=draft|qq=}} [[711]] {{ill|November 3|ja|11月3日|qq=draft|qq=}}) – Under the imperial edict of {{ill|Emperor Genmei|ja|元明天皇|qq=draft|qq=}}, Tai-an Maro began compiling the 【Kojiki】.
* {{ill|Jōō|ja|承応|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=draft|qq=}} [[1652]] {{ill|October 20|ja|10月20日|qq=draft|qq=}}) – Following the ascension of {{ill|Tokugawa Ietsuna|ja|徳川家綱|qq=draft|qq=}}, the era name was changed from {{ill|Keian|ja|慶安|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} to Jōō.
