== Events == * [[:en:Wadō (era)|Wadō]] 4th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[711]] [[:en:November 3|November 3]]) – Under the imperial edict of [[:en:Empress Genmei|Emperor Genmei]], Tai-an Maro began compiling the 【Kojiki】. * [[:en:Jōō (Edo period)|Jōō]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1652|1652]] [[:en:October 20|October 20]]) – Following the ascension of [[:en:Tokugawa Ietsuna|Tokugawa Ietsuna]], the era name was changed from [[:en:Keian|Keian]] to Jōō. == Births == * [[Eiroku]] 5th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1562|1562]] [[:en:February 15|February 15]]) – [[:en:Maeda Toshinaga|Maeda Toshinaga]], 2nd lord of the Kaga Domain (d. [[:en:1614|1614]]). * [[:en:Keiō|Keiō]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1866|1866]] [[:en:February 26|February 26]]) – [[:en:Ekai Kawaguchi|Kawaguchi Ekai]], a Buddhist scholar and explorer of Tibet (d. [[1945]]). * [[Meiji era]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1869|1869]] [[:en:February 22|February 22]]) – [[:en:Okada Saburōsuke|Okada Saburōsuke]], a Western-style painter (d. [[1939]]). == Deaths == * [[:en:Bunkyū|Bunkyū]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1863|1863]] [[:en:October 30|October 30]]) – [[:en:Serizawa Kamo|Serizawa Kamo]], commander of the Shinsengumi (born [[:en:1826|1826]]).
