{{afc comment|Wikidata entry [[d:Q840287]] Wikidata name: 18th day of the 9th month in the Chinese calendar [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 09:13, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} {{Not to be confused with|September 18|qq=September 18}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=九月十八|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 9월 18일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar September|qq=}} '''September 18''' is the 18th day of month {{ill|September (Lunisolar)|ja|9月 (旧暦)|lt=September (Nagatsuki)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/September (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 9th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Tomobiki|qid=Q96759840}}{{efn|ja|友引|1=Rokuyō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q9418169}}{{efn|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tomobiki|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 六曜|1=Rokuyō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q9418169}}.
== Events == * [[:en:Wadō (era)|Wadō]] 4th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:711|711]] [[:en:November 3|November 3]]) – Under the imperial edict of [[:en:Empress Genmei|Emperor Genmei]], Tai-an Maro began compiling the 【Kojiki】. * [[:en:Jōō (Edo period)|Jōō]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1652|1652]] [[:en:October 20|October 20]]) – Following the ascension of [[:en:Tokugawa Ietsuna|Tokugawa Ietsuna]], the era name was changed from [[:en:Keian|Keian]] to Jōō. == Births == * [[:en:Eiroku|Eiroku]] 5th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1562|1562]] [[:en:February 15|February 15]]) – [[:en:Maeda Toshinaga|Maeda Toshinaga]], 2nd lord of the Kaga Domain (d. [[:en:1614|1614]]). * [[:en:Keiō|Keiō]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1866|1866]] [[:en:February 26|February 26]]) – [[:en:Ekai Kawaguchi|Kawaguchi Ekai]], a Buddhist scholar and explorer of Tibet (d. [[:en:1945|1945]]). * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1869|1869]] [[:en:February 22|February 22]]) – [[:en:Okada Saburōsuke|Okada Saburōsuke]], a Western-style painter (d. [[:en:1939|1939]]). == Deaths == * [[:en:Bunkyū|Bunkyū]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1863|1863]] [[:en:October 30|October 30]]) – [[:en:Serizawa Kamo|Serizawa Kamo]], commander of the Shinsengumi (born [[:en:1826|1826]]).
